snippet.textDisplay:
An idea for the $ 70,000: I have organized two fundraising events through an organization called the St. Baldrick's Foundation. This foundation is dedicated to Childhood Cancer research and awareness. what basically happens is the volunteers(also called Shavees) raise money over the course of a few months. then when it comes time for the event, all of the volunteers have their heads shaved in solidarity with all those impacted by this disease. The entire event embraces leaving your comfort zone in order to relate with and show respect and love for the millions of children who are impacted. A few examples of this are how we have had several women participate and lead in the event, getting their heads shaved. During my senior year in high school, I organized the event for the first time. It was the greatest experience and accomplishment of my life. My high school is very small. (less than 200 students in total) Despite our small size, we managed to have over 30 shavees participate and together, we raised over $20,000, far surpassing our goal of $7,000. It was an amazing example of a close, tight-knit community coming together in support of an amazing cause. I would love to be able to host/ see Yes Theory host a massive event where the entire yes fam comes together and raises even more money in addition to the money already won. There could also be several "Rock the Bald" events hosted all over the world. they could be organized and led by leading members of the yes theory family. (maybe from the Facebook group?) 

Sorry if this is too ambitious, but its something that means a great deal to me. It would be an absolute dream of mine to organize this or even see it happen. Regardless of where the money goes, I know it will be massively impactful to some parts of this world. Keep on inspiring others like me!!!
All love from Connecticut

- Steve
